<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Scrabble Club Etiquette — Behaviour Norms & Unwritten Rules</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">Walking into a Scrabble club for the first time can be intimidating — there's a whole set of unwritten rules that regulars take for granted. This guide covers everything from tile handling to challenge protocols so you can focus on playing, not worrying about social missteps.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Before the Game</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Arrive on time:</span> Most clubs start promptly at the posted time. Arriving late disrupts pairings and delays everyone. If you'll be late, text the club director — they may hold your spot.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Bring your own equipment:</span> While clubs usually provide boards, bringing your own tile bag, rack, and score pad shows you're serious. A clock is appreciated for timed games.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Greet your opponent:</span> Introduce yourself, shake hands, wish them good luck. Even in competitive play, sportsmanship starts before the first tile is drawn.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">During the Game</h2>

<div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
  <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
    <thead class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800">
      <tr>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Do</th>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Don't</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100 dark:divide-gray-800">
      <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3">Announce your score clearly after each play</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Mumble or skip score announcements</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3">Keep tiles face-down when drawing from the bag</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Peek at tiles or fish around the bag</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3">Say "hold" before opponent draws if you want to challenge</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Challenge after they've already drawn new tiles</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3">Keep your rack angled so only you can see it</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Leave tiles visible or flash them accidentally</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3">Stay seated and quiet during opponent's turn</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Get up, talk loudly, or distract others mid-game</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Challenge Protocol</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-purple-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">🧩 Challenge Steps</p>
  <div class="space-y-3">
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">1</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Say "hold" or "I challenge" immediately after the word is placed, before opponent draws new tiles.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">2</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Both players agree on the word(s) being challenged. Write them down if needed.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">3</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Look up in the official dictionary (or electronic word judge). Typically the non-challenging player does the lookup.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">4</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">If invalid: player removes the word and loses their turn. If valid: challenger loses their turn (double-challenge rules) or play continues (single-challenge rules).</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10">
  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">📚 Dig Deeper</p>
