<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">After the Game</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Shake hands:</span> Win or lose, shake hands and say "good game." Comment on a specific play you admired — it builds community and shows respect for your opponent's skill.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Report scores:</span> Give your final scores to the club director promptly. Include spread (winning score minus losing score) — it affects ratings.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Post-game analysis:</span> It's fine to discuss interesting plays after the game — most players enjoy it. But don't lecture or criticise your opponent's moves unless they specifically ask for feedback.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Common Etiquette Mistakes</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
    <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Coaching kibitzers</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Spectators must never comment on games in progress — no gasps at missed plays, no hints, no pointing at the board.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
    <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Slamming tiles</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Placing tiles aggressively or loudly signals frustration and is considered poor sportsmanship. Place tiles gently.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
    <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Silent focus</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Keep conversation to between games. During play, focus entirely on the board — respect your opponent's concentration.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
    <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Graceful challenges</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Say "I'd like to challenge" calmly and clearly. Never mock or belittle the word being challenged — you might be wrong.</p>
  </div>
</div>

